description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Newcastle upon Tyne Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is seeking a full-time Healthcare Science Associate Practitioner (HCSAP) to assist Biomedical Scientists in the Immunocytochemistry section of Cellular Pathology at the Royal Victoria Infirmary.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The laboratory is one of the largest services in the country and handles around 80,000 histology requests and 5000 Non-Gynae Cytology requests per annum. We receive a broad range of specimens from within the Trust, General Practitioners and as a specialist referral centre, handle cases regionally, nationally and from overseas. We have a large scope of practice, with specialist sections in Specimen Reception dissection, Slide Production, Immunohistochemistry, Neuropathology, Muscle and Nerve, Electron Microscopy, Non-Gynae Cytology, Autopsy Pathology, Paediatric Pathology, Bio-banking and Research. We are also working towards supporting the Northern Genomic Laboratory Hub as regional Pathology centre, advancing in molecular techniques. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The applicant must be able to demonstrate practical experience of working within a Cellular Pathology laboratory to include practical experience of receipt, preparation and staining of histology and non- diagnostic cytology samples. Applicants must meet the essential criteria of having NVQ level 4 qualifications or equivalent level of experience, including, for example, handling tissue/fluids or microtomy. In addition operation and maintenance of automated staining equipment will be part of the role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working hours are flexible to the service need, within the laboratory opening hours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post offers excellent, progressive opportunities for both skills development and career enhancement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We pride ourselves in meeting service needs effectively, with quality and service innovation central to our delivery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full time 37 hours 30 minutes/week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
